{{Infobox UK place | official_name = Birmingham Business Park | static_image_name = Birmingham Business Park.jpg | static_image_caption = Aerial view | coordinates = {{coord|52.469|-1.719|type:landmark_dim:2000|display=inline,title}} | country = England | region = West Midlands | population = | population_ref = | post_town = BIRMINGHAM | postcode_area = B | postcode_district = B37, B40 | dial_code = 0121 | constituency_westminster = [[Meriden (UK Parliament constituency)|Meriden]] | civil_parish = [[Bickenhill and Marston Green]] | metropolitan_borough = [[Metropolitan Borough of Solihull|Solihull]] | metropolitan_county = [[West Midlands (county)|West Midlands]] }}
'''Birmingham Business Park''' is the most established out-of-town office park in the [[The Midlands|Midlands]] and is home to 116 companies, over 7000 employees and is the European and UK office headquarters for over 20 organisations. Its range of high profile occupiers include [[Rolls Royce]], [[Fujitsu]], [[EE Limited|EE]], [[Dunlop Tyres]] ([[HiQ (tyres)|HiQ]]), and [[IMI]]. The Park offers 24 hour security and an on-site management team.
Centrally located off Junction 6 of the [[M42 motorway|M42]] and Junction 4 of [[M6 motorway|M6]], it has immediate access to the Midlands motorway network with direct links into [[Birmingham city centre]]. [[Birmingham International railway station|Birmingham International Railway Station]] and [[Birmingham Airport|Airport]] are minutes away offering rail and air links.
Set within 148 acres of landscaped gardens the Park maintains nature walks, two beehives and a flower garden as well as encouraging tenants to use public transport, walking and cycling routes.
There is also an on-site cafe and newsagent as well as catering vans that deliver to the door. A selection of health and fitness classes run throughout the week, including pilates and relaxation.
