{{for|people named De Cecco|De Cecco (surname)}} {{infobox company |logo = Logo De Cecco.jpg |location = [[Fara San Martino]] |industry = pasta |founded = 1886 }} '''De Cecco''' is an [[Italy|Italian]] company producing dried pasta, flour and other related food products.
==History== The company was founded in 1886 by the De Cecco brothers in the small town of [[Fara San Martino]] in the [[Abruzzo]] region of central [[Italy]]. Nicola De Cecco originally produced flour at his stone mill before establishing the pasta factory.<ref name="Routledge">{{cite book|author1=Augusta Consorti |author2=Luciano D'Amico |author3=Massimo Sargiacomo |title=Accounting and Food: Some Italian Experiences|publisher=Routledge, 2016|isbn=131722843X|pages=42-68|chapter=Accounting and Management in the Pasta Industry. The De Cecco Case (1886–1955)}}</ref>
In 1908, the company adopted a country girl with a wheat stacks as its trademark. After World War II the factory was rebuilt after being destroyed by German bomb attacks. In 1950 De Cecco completed a new factory in [[Pescara]] to meet the increased demand that occurred after the war. In 1980, a new production facility was opened in [[Fara San Martino]], doubling the company's production output. In 1986 the company began to diversify its offerings by establishing its olive oil brand. De Cecco offerings have since expanded to sauces, grains and tomato based products.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Paola Pierucci|title=L'impresa familiare nel Mezzogiorno continentale fra passato e presente. Un approccio interdisciplinare|publisher=Franco Angeli, 2007|isbn=8856819376|url=https://books.google.it/books?id=8xWWLrAqg5oC&dq=%22de+cecco%22+++olio+extra+vergine&source=gbs_navlinks_s|chapter=L'impresa familiare in Abruzzo. Il caso della De Cecco}}</ref>
As of 2013, De Cecco is the third largest pasta producer in the world.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Andrea Guccione|title=Consuma meridionale: Un manifesto per il sud|publisher=Imprimatur, 2013|isbn=886830113X|url=https://books.google.it/books?id=ljVQAwAAQBAJ&pg=PT72&dq=1886++%22de+cecco%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwje6tzstorQAhUlI8AKHUL-AckQ6AEIGzAA#v=onepage&q=1886%20%20%22de%20cecco%22&f=false}}</ref>
