{{Infobox settlement | official_name = Downtown Melrose | settlement_type = [[Neighborhood]] | image_skyline = Downtown Melrose.jpg | imagesize = 250px | image_caption = Downtown Melrose seen from the intersection of Upham and Main Streets facing south | image_flag = | image_seal = | nickname = | motto = | image_map = | map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|42|27|17|N|71|03|56|W|region:US_type:city|display=inline,title}} | subdivision_type = [[List of sovereign states|Country]] | subdivision_name = United States | subdivision_type1 = [[U.S. state|State]] | subdivision_name1 = [[Massachusetts]] | subdivision_type2 = [[List of counties in Massachusetts|County]] | subdivision_name2 = [[Middlesex County, Massachusetts|Middlesex]] | subdivision_type3 = [[List of municipalities in Massachusetts|City]] | subdivision_name3 = [[Melrose, Massachusetts|Melrose]] | established_title = | established_date = | government_type = | leader_title = | leader_name = | area_total_km2 = | area_total_sq_mi = | area_land_km2 = | area_land_sq_mi = | area_water_km2 = | area_water_sq_mi = | elevation_m = | elevation_ft = | population_total = | population_as_of = | population_density_km2 = | population_density_sq_mi = | timezone = [[Eastern Standard Time Zone|Eastern]] | utc_offset = -5 | timezone_DST = [[Eastern Standard Time Zone|Eastern]] | utc_offset_DST = -4 | postal_code_type = ZIP code | postal_code = 02176 | area_code = [[Area code 339|339]] / [[Area code 781|781]] | website = {{URL|http://www.cityofmelrose.org}} | footnotes = {{Infobox NRHP | name = Melrose Town Center Historic District | embed = yes | nrhp_type = hd | nocat = yes | image = | caption = | location = Main St., [[Melrose, Massachusetts]] | locmapin = Massachusetts | architect = Multiple | architecture = Late 19th And 20th Century Revivals, Late Victorian | added = April 1, 1982 | area = {{convert|8|acre}} | refnum = 82002744<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }} }} '''Downtown Melrose''' is the [[central business district]] of [[Melrose, Massachusetts|Melrose]], [[Massachusetts]]. It is known for its nineteenth century [[Victorian architecture]] and its many small family-owned stores. Downtown Melrose is generally classified as the area on Main Street from Grove Street to Essex/Upham Streets. Part of the area, running on Main Street just northeast of the junction with Upham and Essex Streets, is included in the '''Melrose Town Center Historic District''', which was added to the [[National Register of Historic Places]] on April 1, 1982.<ref name="nris"/> This district encompasses seven buildings, including city hall, the main fire station, Memorial Hall, the Coolidge School, and the Baptist and Methodist churches.<ref name=NRHP>{{cite web|url=http://mhc-macris.net/Details.aspx?MhcId=MEL.B|title=NRHP nomination for Melrose Center Historic District|publisher=Commonwealth of Massachusetts|accessdate=2014-02-26}}</ref>
