'''Taylor, Fladgate & Yeatman''' (often simply '''Taylor Fladgate''') is one of the largest [[port wine]] houses.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.intowine.com/port2.html|title=Port Wine Producer Profiles - Into Wine|publisher=|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref> Founded in 1692 in [[Vila Nova de Gaia]], [[Portugal]] by Job Bearsley, becoming Taylor, Fladgate & Yeatman when Joseph Taylor, [[John Alexander Fladgate]] and Morgan Yeatman formed a partnership in 1838, it is also one of the oldest.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atlasofwineries.com/wineries/taylorfladgate.html|title=AN ATLAS OF WINERIES|publisher=|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref> The house owns the brands of Fonseca, [[Fonseca-Guimaraens]], Taylor, Krohn and Croft.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.croftport.com/history.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-01-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130127105219/http://www.croftport.com/history.htm |archivedate=2013-01-27 |df= }}</ref> The house ships almost all types of port including vintage, tawny, ruby, late-bottled vintage, and white. The house invented the style of late-bottled vintage port.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.taylor.pt/|title=Taylor's Port Wine - The Home of Port|first=Taylor's|last=Port|publisher=|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref> Taylor Fladgate's vintage ports are some of the most sought-after and expensive ports in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kobrandwineandspirits.com/products/view_factsheet.php?c=tfg000|title=Kobrand Wine & Spirits - Portfolio - All Brands|publisher=|accessdate=2 August 2016}}</ref>{{Failed verification|date=May 2017}}
